Cape Peninsula University of Technology students are threatening to shut down the institution. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports. #eNCA #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - The Cape Peninsula University of Technology students are threatening to shut down the institution. Their concerns are mostly related to student accommodation. The university's SRC claims there are hundreds of students sleeping in corridors. The University insists this is not the case. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos has the details in the video above.